Special Adviser to the Osun State Governor on Civic Engagement, Olatunbosun Oyintiloye, has said his principal, Adegboyega Oyetola, was not feeling tensed ahead of the July 16 governorship poll. He said there was no tension because masses were in support of Oyetola’s reelection. Oyintiloye spoke at a civic engagement meeting organised by the State’s Civic Engagement office and Association of Master Bakers, Osun Chapter in Osogbo on Sunday. A statement by Oyintiloye, who represented Oyetola at the meeting titled, ‘I will be reelected because I have kept promises made to Osun people, says Oyetola,’ further said the Osun helmsman has kept all promises made to the people of the state before he was elected in 2018. He said the governor would continue to focus on quality service delivery to the people if reelected, adding that Oyetola would not relax, but would work harder for a better condition of living for the residents. “Because the masses are behind him, Governor Oyetola is approaching the poll with no tension at all and they will return him to office. “He has have kept promises made to the good people of Osun and I know that they will keep their promise to return him on the election date. “He will not in any relax in his second term in office, but he will rather continue to build on the solid foundation he has laid,” he said Appealing to members of the association to collect their Permanent Voter Cards, Oyintiloye also urged them to support Oyetola’s re-election. In his remarks, the chairman of the association, Bakare Ganiyu commended the governor for various developmental projects in the state and promised that his members would support Oyetola’s re-election bid. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com